The paper discusses the interpretability of machine learning models in the context of EEG decoding, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the study investigates how ConvNets represent spectral features, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
